               Meng, Jianghong and Brown, Eric W",
  abstract  = "Water is vital to agriculture. It is essential that the water
               used for the production of fresh produce commodities be safe.
               Microbial pathogens are able to survive for extended periods of
               time in water. It is critical to understand their biology and
               ecology in this ecosystem in order to develop better mitigation
               strategies for farmers who grow these food crops. In this review
